cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with optimization problems in social networks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of submodular functions and stochastic optimization suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The introduction of a new optimization problem and its reduction from another problem suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
